Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens; roughly chop whites. Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered). Trim and halve @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (quarter any larger mushrooms; skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

== Bacon ==

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

== Fries ==

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @Old Bay seasoning{1%unit} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, flipping halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Slaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, scallion greens, @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

== Spicy Remoulade ==

In a second medium bowl, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{4%teaspoon}, scallion whites, juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste.

== Tempura Mushrooms ==

In a third medium bowl, whisk together @tempura batter{82%g}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining Old Bay seasoning, @cold water{1/3%cup} (2/3 cup for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{}. (TIP: If mixture is too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.) Stir mushrooms into batter until fully coated.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, use #tongs{} to add coated mushrooms in a single layer. TIP: Work in batches if necessary.

Cook until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on first side and ~{1-2%minutes} on second side. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer mushrooms to a paper-towel-lined plate. Season with salt.

> Use pan used for bacon here.

== Toasted Baguettes ==

While mushrooms cook, halve @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through.

Toast, cut sides up (place directly on oven rack or use a baking sheet), until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Spread cut sides of baguettes with spicy remoulade; fill with mushrooms, @sliced dill pickle{1}, and as much slaw as you like.

Divide sandwiches and fries between #plates{}. Serve with any remaining slaw, any remaining remoulade, and remaining lemon wedges on the side. TIP: If you've got some on hand, serve ketchup or malt vinegar with your fries!

> Top sandwiches with bacon.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.